---
import BaseHead from '../../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import HeaderEn from '../../../components/HeaderEn.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/Footer.astro';
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <BaseHead
    title="Family Law Mediation Lawyer Ontario | ADR · Settlement | Miao He"
    description="Certified mediator and experienced litigator. Strategic out-of-court settlement, mediation-arbitration, JRP representation. Mandarin and English. 647-930-6688."
  />
  <meta name="keywords" content="family law mediation Ontario,divorce mediation Toronto,mediation arbitration Ontario,out of court settlement family law,JRP family lawyer,certified mediator Ontario" />
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://www.miaohelaw.ca/en/family-law/mediation" />
  <link rel="alternate" hreflang="zh" href="https://www.miaohelaw.ca/family-law/mediation" />
  <link rel="alternate" hreflang="en" href="https://www.miaohelaw.ca/en/family-law/mediation" />
  <style>
    *{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}body{font-family:Georgia,serif;background:#FDFBF7;color:#E8D5B0}a{color:inherit;text-decoration:none}
    .lang-bar{background:#ffffff;text-align:right;padding:.4rem 2rem;font-size:.8rem}.lang-bar a{color:#5A4A3A;margin-left:1rem}.lang-bar a.active{color:#8B6914;font-weight:600}
    .page{max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;padding:3rem 2rem}
    .breadcrumb{font-size:.78rem;color:#7A6A5A;margin-bottom:2rem}.breadcrumb a{color:#D4A853}
    h1{font-size:2rem;color:#1A1208;margin-bottom:.5rem}
    .lead{color:#5A4A3A;font-size:1rem;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:2rem}
    .card{background:#ffffff;border:1px solid #E8E0D5;border-radius:8px;padding:2rem;margin-bottom:1.5rem}
    .card h2{color:#8B6914;font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:1rem;letter-spacing:.05em}
    .card p{color:#5A4A3A;font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:.8rem}
    .card ul{list-style:none;padding:0}.card ul li{color:#5A4A3A;font-size:.85rem;padding:.3rem 0 .3rem 1.2rem;position:relative}.card ul li::before{content:"·";position:absolute;left:0;color:#D4A853}
    .faq-item{border-bottom:1px solid #3A3020;padding:1rem 0}.faq-item:last-child{border-bottom:none}
    .faq-q{color:#1A1208;font-size:.9rem;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:.4rem}
    .faq-a{color:#7A6A5A;font-size:.83rem;line-height:1.7}
    .cta{text-align:center;padding:2rem}.cta h2{color:#8B6914;margin-bottom:1rem}
    .btn-primary{display:inline-block;background:#D4A853;color:#1A1208;padding:.75rem 2rem;border-radius:6px;font-weight:700;margin:.5rem}
    .btn-secondary{display:inline-block;border:1px solid #D4A853;color:#8B6914;padding:.75rem 2rem;border-radius:6px;margin:.5rem}
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="lang-bar"><a href="/family-law/mediation">中文</a><a href="/en/family-law/mediation" class="active">EN</a></div>
  <HeaderEn />
  <div class="page">
    <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/en/">Home</a> › Family Law › Mediation & ADR</div>
    <h1>Mediation & Alternative Dispute Resolution</h1>
    <p class="lead">The best outcome does not always come from the courtroom. A litigator who can also mediate gives you the full picture — and the strongest position at every stage.</p>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>WHAT WE OFFER</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Strategic mediation support — as your lawyer at the table</li>
        <li>Mediation-arbitration (Med-Arb)</li>
        <li>Judicial Dispute Resolution (JDR / JRP) representation</li>
        <li>Four-way meetings and settlement conferences</li>
        <li>Minutes of Settlement drafting</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>VERIFIED OUTCOME</h2>
      <p>$1,000,000+ settlement achieved through mediation for a client in a high-conflict family law dispute. The case had been in litigation for years before reaching a resolution at the mediation table.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</h2>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Is mediation binding?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Mediation itself is not binding — it is a voluntary process. However, if the parties reach an agreement and sign a Minutes of Settlement or Separation Agreement, that document becomes legally binding.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Can the other side refuse to participate in mediation?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. Mediation and other ADR processes require both parties to agree voluntarily. Courts cannot force a party to mediate, unlike a court hearing where attendance can be compelled.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Is mediation cheaper than litigation?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">It depends. Mediation can save significant time and legal fees if both parties are ready to negotiate in good faith. However, if mediation breaks down, the parties still need to litigate — which means additional costs. We help you assess which path makes sense for your situation.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card cta">
      <h2>Book a Consultation</h2>
      <a href="tel:6479306688" class="btn-primary">📞 647-930-6688</a>
      <a href="mailto:miao@miaohelaw.ca" class="btn-secondary">Email Us</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <Footer />
</body>
</html>
